        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(channels): default boundary logger for swallowed progress-draft start errors",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nReplacement for #92031 (closed). Timer-fired progress-draft start failures were\nswallowed because the `onStartError` hook on `createChannelProgressDraftGate` was\noptional and no production caller (compositor, Slack, Matrix, MS Teams) passed one.\n\nPer the close note, this takes the **default-logger-at-the-helper-boundary** path:\n`createChannelProgressDraftGate` now defaults `onStartError` to a boundary logger\n(`logWarn`), so the failure is observed for **every** caller without threading a\ncallback through each channel. Callers may still pass their own `onStartError` to\noverride.\n\n- Files: `src/channels/streaming.ts` (+ tests).\n- No `CHANGELOG.md` edit (release-only per `AGENTS.md`).\n\n## Why core (not ClawHub)\n\nCore stability fix in `src/channels/**` (shared channel streaming); not an optional\nskill bundle.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/channels/streaming.test.ts src/channels/progress-draft-compositor.test.ts` => **13 passed**\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` (tsconfig.core.json) => clean\n- `oxfmt --check` + `oxlint` on touched files => clean\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** a timer-fired progress-draft start rejection is now logged at the gate boundary for every caller (not only when a caller opts into `onStartError`).\n- **Real environment tested:** macOS (Darwin 25.3.0); OpenClaw at latest `main`; Node 22; Vitest.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/channels/streaming.test.ts src/channels/progress-draft-compositor.test.ts`\n- **Evidence after fix:** 13 tests pass, including a new **integration-level** regression that drives the real `createChannelProgressDraftCompositor` (which builds the gate with no `onStartError`) with a rejecting `update`, fires the delayed-start timer, and asserts the boundary `logWarn` fires; plus a gate-level default test.\n- **Observed result after fix:** the compositor's swallowed timer-start failure is now reported via `logWarn(\"channel progress draft failed to start: ...\")` instead of disappearing.\n- **What was not tested:** end-to-end delivery on a live Slack/Matrix/MS Teams transport; Linux CI. The fix is at the shared gate boundary, so all those callers inherit it.\n\nRefs: #92031.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
        "branch": "fix/streaming-progress-start-error",
